{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0433bc2f-af36-474f-872c-431a72adc97a","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NUnit3TestAdapter** to **v5.0.0+** — this version adds Microsoft.Testing.Platform support.\n\n2. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Add a property** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and is no longer needed (Microsoft.Testing.Platform has its own).\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly via the built executable.\n\n> **Note:** NUnit3TestAdapter 5.0+ generates a `Program.cs` entry point automatically via source generators. If you have a custom `Main`, you may need to reconcile it.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"abfa4921-5d1e-4bd9-a85a-a90d557746d4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly based on my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":336,"requestId":"0434:1CDF9E:1E5713B:2220C0F:69E81959"},"id":"5e220c5f-5889-4e2b-9e84-c07b20362d9e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:11.219Z","parentId":"2e5395b8-db95-47dc-aece-fa65b8a6c9d4"}
